Monitoring and observability using AWS Prometheus and Grafana.

AWS Prometheus and Grafana for setting up monitoring and observability on AWS EKS cluster level.

-	For AWS Prometheus Amp workspace creation for data managed by aws with respective workspace id and workspace remote write URL for access.
-	Enable aws managed scrapper for collecting metrics and configure it for eks cluster.
-	Grained access using Iam for user and service access in aws.
And.
-	Data ingested to amp workspace through scrappers.
-	Create Grafana a workspace for observability dashboard
-	Integrating Grafana workspace to aws Prometheus workspace by adding data source using AMP endpoint/access point. 
-	Import dashboard for Kubernetes pod node service metrics.

CloudWatch and can be implemented to monitor over cluster behaviour and metrics and integrated service for monitoring auditing can be done using CloudTrail AWS Config is a better option to go with precise fine grained implementation for project compliance.
